/*!

<!---------------------------------------------------------------------------->

\mainpage Overview of the stdheaders package
\version draco-5_1_0
\author Michelle Murillo Thomas M. Evans

stdheaders provides C++ Standard defined headers for the ANSI C-STD
library.  The C++ standard stipulates that c-std libraries,
ie. math.h, should sit in the std namespace and be called using
c(library name).  Thus, cos from math.h is called using std::cos from
cmath.

stdheaders is turned on by the --enable-draco-stdhdrs option.

<!---------------------------------------------------------------------------->

